"Oden Shop"
I won't drink anymore!

58
00:03:41,394 --> 00:03:44,030
"Oden Shop"
I understand,
so let's go home, Father.

59
00:03:44,030 --> 00:03:45,520
"Oden Shop"

60
00:03:48,435 --> 00:03:51,131
Hajime, what kind of flower is that?

61
00:03:57,410 --> 00:03:59,512
Red spider lilies, aren't they?

62
00:03:59,512 --> 00:04:01,207
Red spider lilies...

63
00:04:23,637 --> 00:04:24,797
Let's hurry.

64
00:04:31,011 --> 00:04:33,275
Damn guy showed up, as expected.

65
00:04:35,849 --> 00:04:37,350
Mr. Murai!

66
00:04:37,350 --> 00:04:39,753
Mr. Murai!

67
00:04:39,753 --> 00:04:41,448
I wonder if they're not home.

68
00:04:44,024 --> 00:04:45,457
Mr. Murai?

69
00:04:47,260 --> 00:04:49,329
Yuko?

70
00:04:49,329 --> 00:04:50,990
Is no one here?

71
00:04:56,369 --> 00:04:57,859
Miss Yuko!

72
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:08,575
Tsugumi...

73
00:05:17,691 --> 00:05:19,090
Mr. Murai...

74
00:05:25,932 --> 00:05:27,334
Do you want some more?

75
00:05:27,334 --> 00:05:29,536
No, thank you.

76
00:05:29,536 --> 00:05:32,405
How are you doing?
Feeling a little better?

77
00:05:32,405 --> 00:05:34,274
Yes...

78
00:05:34,274 --> 00:05:36,276
What in the world happened?

79
00:05:36,276 --> 00:05:38,767
I was totally under the impression
that the farm was going well.

80
00:05:43,817 --> 00:05:45,518
Won't you tell us?

81
00:05:45,518 --> 00:05:46,780
Yuko...

82
00:05:50,490 --> 00:05:53,226
It was two years ago...

83
00:05:53,226 --> 00:05:56,525
Right after we'd moved here.

84
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:02,300
There we go...

85
00:06:09,442 --> 00:06:10,777
Whoa!

86
00:06:10,777 --> 00:06:12,642
That was close.

87
00:06:14,147 --> 00:06:15,512
Father!

88
00:06:17,684 --> 00:06:20,053
Working hard there, I see!

89
00:06:20,053 --> 00:06:22,956
The man's name was Ryosuke Sekine.

90
00:06:22,956 --> 00:06:25,759
He lived on the other
side of the farm.

91
00:06:25,759 --> 00:06:28,061
I apologize for my earlier behavior.

92
00:06:28,061 --> 00:06:30,130
Maybe it's because I used
to work for a publishing company,

93
00:06:30,130 --> 00:06:32,899
but I have this habit of
being suspicious of strangers.

94
00:06:32,899 --> 00:06:36,503
And it doesn't seem like
we're very welcome here, so...

95
00:06:36,503 --> 00:06:37,697
Thank you for the food.

96
00:06:40,673 --> 00:06:42,140
It's delicious!

97
00:06:44,911 --> 00:06:46,413
Here you go.

98
00:06:46,413 --> 00:06:48,347
Oh, no, not me.

99
00:06:49,482 --> 00:06:53,019
I've had a lot of bad experiences,
so I don't drink anymore.

100
00:06:53,019 --> 00:06:56,182
Is that right? That's too bad.

101
00:07:00,026 --> 00:07:03,730
But quitting a company job!
That's quite a daring move.

102
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:07,867
I inherited this vast place
from my uncle, after all.

103
00:07:07,867 --> 00:07:10,770
It would be a shame
to just let it sit here.

104
00:07:10,770 --> 00:07:12,872
And ever since I lost my wife,

105
00:07:12,872 --> 00:07:15,642
I've had to leave my little girl
here alone so much.

106
00:07:15,642 --> 00:07:19,746
I thought I could be around
for her a little more out here.

107
00:07:19,746 --> 00:07:21,714
We're going to grow vegetables.

108
00:07:21,714 --> 00:07:26,219
We're complete amateurs,
so I'm sure it won't be easy,

109
00:07:26,219 --> 00:07:29,122
but we decided we'd work
hard at it together. Right?

110
00:07:29,122 --> 00:07:31,291
Yup.

111
00:07:31,291 --> 00:07:33,793
In that case, I might be able
to offer you some advice.

112
00:07:33,793 --> 00:07:36,396
Since I used to do it long ago, too.

113
00:07:36,396 --> 00:07:37,897
Really?!

114
00:07:37,897 --> 00:07:39,666
I don't know how much
help I'll be...

115
00:07:39,666 --> 00:07:43,169
Isn't that great, Yuko?
He says he'll lend us a hand.

116
00:07:43,169 --> 00:07:44,637
Yeah!

117
00:07:44,637 --> 00:07:49,509
After that, he began to
come to our place every day.

118
00:07:49,509 --> 00:07:53,346
How to work the field.
How to pick seeds.

119
00:07:53,346 --> 00:07:56,249
Even how to water
and fertilize the plants.

120
00:07:56,249 --> 00:07:58,581
He was very generous
in teaching us.

121
00:08:03,790 --> 00:08:06,426
In town, we'd be treated
as outsiders.

122
00:08:06,426 --> 00:08:10,419
For Father, that man was the
only person he had to talk to.

123
00:08:11,531 --> 00:08:12,899
Thanks to that man,

124
00:08:12,899 --> 00:08:15,635
even in what was supposed to
be a difficult first year,

125
00:08:15,635 --> 00:08:18,297
we were able to grow
really delicious vegetables.

126
00:08:22,642 --> 00:08:24,711
I still remember it now.

127
00:08:24,711 --> 00:08:27,908
Father looked really
happy that day.

128
00:08:33,653 --> 00:08:37,757
That night, the man convinced
my unwilling father...

129
00:08:37,757 --> 00:08:40,727
...and forced him
to expand the farm.

130
00:08:40,727 --> 00:08:41,921
And then...

131
00:08:44,230 --> 00:08:46,065
We had abnormal weather
conditions this year...

132
00:08:46,065 --> 00:08:48,124
...and there were lots of pests.

133
00:08:49,536 --> 00:08:50,770
Mr. Sekine...

134
00:08:50,770 --> 00:08:53,706
We should've used pesticide.

135
00:08:53,706 --> 00:08:57,176
We don't have room for that
kind of thing in our budget yet.

136
00:08:57,176 --> 00:09:00,013
Necessity knows no law, right?

137
00:09:00,013 --> 00:09:03,149
I imagine it's expensive...
Pesticide...

138
00:09:03,149 --> 00:09:04,817
It's still not too late.

139
00:09:04,817 --> 00:09:08,121
I'll let you have some
of the stuff I used to use.

140
00:09:08,121 --> 00:09:09,622
R-Really?!

141
00:09:09,622 --> 00:09:11,858
Please don't be shy.
Let's do our best!

142
00:09:11,858 --> 00:09:13,883
Th-Thank you very much!

143
00:09:22,368 --> 00:09:25,471
Father believed what
the man told him...

144
00:09:25,471 --> 00:09:27,574
...and used the pesticide
every day,

145
00:09:27,574 --> 00:09:29,906
but the vegetables kept dying
one after another.

146
00:09:35,348 --> 00:09:39,341
It was around then that
Father started drinking again.

147
00:09:43,656 --> 00:09:46,859
I still say it'd be better if
we consulted other people, too!

148
00:09:46,859 --> 00:09:49,696
At this rate,
they're all really going to die!

149
00:09:49,696 --> 00:09:53,333
It'll be okay. As long as
we do as Mr. Sekine says...

150
00:09:53,333 --> 00:09:54,664
Father!

151
00:09:57,537 --> 00:10:00,740
It'll be okay. No worries.

152
00:10:00,740 --> 00:10:02,537
It'll be okay.

153
00:10:06,546 --> 00:10:10,850
In the end, Father didn't
go consult anyone else...

154
00:10:10,850 --> 00:10:13,683
...and kept on waiting for the
pesticide to start taking effect.

155
00:10:24,931 --> 00:10:27,399
I wonder if he got lost
and wandered in here.

156
00:10:31,037 --> 00:10:33,505
Oh, no! You can't lick that stuff!

157
00:10:41,547 --> 00:10:43,483
What...

158
00:10:43,483 --> 00:10:44,814
...does this mean?

159
00:10:46,753 --> 00:10:47,811
Father?!

160
00:11:08,307 --> 00:11:12,545
He told us it was a pesticide
that would kill the insects,

161
00:11:12,545 --> 00:11:16,675
but he'd been giving us a solution
of just juice mixed with water.

162
00:11:18,117 --> 00:11:23,523
Not knowing that, Father completely
believed it was real pesticide...

163
00:11:23,523 --> 00:11:26,526
Why did that man
do something like that?

164
00:11:26,526 --> 00:11:28,928
I heard about it
and found out later...

165
00:11:28,928 --> 00:11:33,099
...that he used to be in a dispute with
Father's late uncle over this land.

166
00:11:33,099 --> 00:11:35,090
It was revenge?

167
00:11:36,836 --> 00:11:40,273
Why did Father have to die?

168
00:11:40,273 --> 00:11:44,644
Moving in to a new house,
starting a new line of work...

169
00:11:44,644 --> 00:11:47,306
We only wanted to live normally!

170
00:11:48,648 --> 00:11:50,650
And that's why you accessed the site?

171
00:11:50,650 --> 00:11:52,985
What?

172
00:11:52,985 --> 00:11:54,646
The Hell Link site...

173
00:12:12,205 --> 00:12:14,707
You were given a straw doll, right?

174
00:12:14,707 --> 00:12:17,335
That you can get revenge
if you pull the thread?

175
00:12:21,647 --> 00:12:23,850
I understand how you
feel really well,

176
00:12:23,850 --> 00:12:25,852
but you shouldn't seek revenge!

177
00:12:25,852 --> 00:12:26,819
Hajime!

178
00:12:26,819 --> 00:12:27,911
Tsugumi, you be quiet!

179
00:12:31,524 --> 00:12:33,259
Listen to me, Yuko.

180
00:12:33,259 --> 00:12:37,697
If you pull that thread,
a person is going to be banished to Hell.

181
00:12:37,697 --> 00:12:40,032
You may be able to get
your revenge that way,

182
00:12:40,032 --> 00:12:42,468
but you'll have banished
someone to Hell.

183
00:12:42,468 --> 00:12:45,238
That fact will never be erased.

184
00:12:45,238 --> 00:12:48,366
You'll have to live with that
burden for the rest of your life.

185
00:12:50,543 --> 00:12:54,035
You can see what a terrible
thing that would be, can't you?

186
00:12:55,982 --> 00:12:58,451
I knew your father well.

187
00:12:58,451 --> 00:13:01,154
He was always talking about you.

188
00:13:01,154 --> 00:13:03,756
All he thought of was your happiness.

189
00:13:03,756 --> 00:13:09,162
That's why I know that your
father wouldn't want revenge.

190
00:13:09,162 --> 00:13:12,165
To say nothing of having you
live the rest of your life...

191
00:13:12,165 --> 00:13:15,100
...with this guilt on your
shoulders for his sake.

192
00:13:18,504 --> 00:13:21,337
This is sort of getting messed up...

193
00:13:33,653 --> 00:13:35,254
Hajime!

194
00:13:35,254 --> 00:13:37,623
I'll hold on to this.

195
00:13:37,623 --> 00:13:39,614
Think this through carefully!

196
00:13:41,928 --> 00:13:45,198
Hey, man, that's foul play,
isn't it?!

197
00:13:45,198 --> 00:13:47,132
We'll just have to get it back.

198
00:14:33,379 --> 00:14:34,744
Father...

199
00:15:09,348 --> 00:15:10,838
Do I smell?

200
00:15:12,285 --> 00:15:13,616
A little.

201
00:15:19,525 --> 00:15:21,994
That wasn't fair.

202
00:15:21,994 --> 00:15:24,597
Taking it away from
her was underhanded!

203
00:15:24,597 --> 00:15:26,766
Yes, it might have
been underhanded.

204
00:15:26,766 --> 00:15:28,567
But please understand.

205
00:15:28,567 --> 00:15:31,070
I don't want Yuko
to seek out revenge.

206
00:15:31,070 --> 00:15:32,371
I don't understand!

207
00:15:32,371 --> 00:15:38,244
Yuko's father was practically
killed by that man!

208
00:15:38,244 --> 00:15:40,413
See, Tsugumi,

209
00:15:40,413 --> 00:15:42,949
there's a lot that happens in life.

210
00:15:42,949 --> 00:15:46,619
And some of it's going to
be unbelievably unjust...

211
00:15:46,619 --> 00:15:49,388
But you have to overcome
those things.

212
00:15:49,388 --> 00:15:51,524
That's what it means to live.

213
00:15:51,524 --> 00:15:54,093
So, it's okay even
if you get killed?

214
00:15:54,093 --> 00:15:55,594
I never said that!

215
00:15:55,594 --> 00:15:57,463
Yes, it's what you're saying!

216
00:15:57,463 --> 00:15:59,999
Why are you taking sides
with a bastard like that?!

217
00:15:59,999 --> 00:16:02,468
He deserves to get sent to Hell!

218
00:16:02,468 --> 00:16:06,405
Yuko's father never
did anything bad...

219
00:16:06,405 --> 00:16:09,101
A bastard like that,
the sooner he dies the better!

220
00:16:16,449 --> 00:16:18,684
You're so pigheaded, Hajime!

221
00:16:18,684 --> 00:16:22,586
If you got killed,
Tsugumi would get revenge, too!

222
00:16:24,590 --> 00:16:25,579
Tsugumi!

223
00:16:47,313 --> 00:16:48,507
Miss.

224
00:16:50,282 --> 00:16:51,306
Wanyuudou...

225
00:16:55,021 --> 00:16:58,090
I didn't expect Tsugumi
to say something like that...

226
00:16:58,090 --> 00:17:00,354
I wonder if it's my fault,
after all.

227
00:17:03,863 --> 00:17:04,964
Rain?

228
00:17:15,508 --> 00:17:16,634
Tsugumi!

229
00:17:17,643 --> 00:17:19,042
Tsugumi!

230
00:17:28,721 --> 00:17:30,086
Father...

231
00:17:36,262 --> 00:17:39,098
Hell Girl!

232
00:17:39,098 --> 00:17:40,766
What should I do?

233
00:17:40,766 --> 00:17:45,135
I don't know. Please tell me!
What should I do?!

234
00:17:46,138 --> 00:17:48,834
That is for you to decide.

235
00:18:28,280 --> 00:18:30,649
I'm just not going to forgive him!

236
00:18:30,649 --> 00:18:32,139
Not him!

237
00:18:33,586 --> 00:18:34,575
Yuko!

238
00:18:37,389 --> 00:18:38,858
Have you seen Tsugumi?

239
00:18:38,858 --> 00:18:39,892
What?

240
00:18:39,892 --> 00:18:41,760
I can't find her anywhere.

241
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:43,662
You can't go that way!

242
00:18:43,662 --> 00:18:45,323
It's dangerous at night!

243
00:18:48,300 --> 00:18:50,302
Tsugumi!

244
00:18:50,302 --> 00:18:53,038
Tsugumi!

245
00:18:53,038 --> 00:18:55,207
Tsugumi!

246
00:18:55,207 --> 00:18:57,076
Tsugumi!

247
00:18:57,076 --> 00:18:59,510
Oh! This is...

248
00:19:01,614 --> 00:19:03,104
It's Tsugumi's.

249
00:19:04,416 --> 00:19:06,441
Tsugumi!

250
00:19:18,330 --> 00:19:19,490
Tsugumi!

251
00:19:20,666 --> 00:19:22,156
Hajime...

252
00:19:24,303 --> 00:19:26,372
You idiot!

253
00:19:26,372 --> 00:19:28,607
Do you have any idea
how worried I was?!

254
00:19:28,607 --> 00:19:30,131
And in this rain...

255
00:19:36,215 --> 00:19:39,707
It's not like I asked you
to worry about me.

256
00:19:41,554 --> 00:19:42,543
Tsugumi!

257
00:19:51,664 --> 00:19:52,995
You idiot...

258
00:19:54,099 --> 00:19:55,589
You made me so worried...

259
00:19:57,469 --> 00:20:01,307
I really was worried, you know...

260
00:20:01,307 --> 00:20:02,968
Hajime...

261
00:20:19,258 --> 00:20:21,427
You're not going to take revenge?

262
00:20:21,427 --> 00:20:24,129
You're really okay with that?

263
00:20:24,129 --> 00:20:26,065
Yeah.

264
00:20:26,065 --> 00:20:27,967
I see. I'm glad.

265
00:20:27,967 --> 00:20:30,903
You've gotta find happiness enough
for both you and your father.

266
00:20:30,903 --> 00:20:33,405
Thank you.

267
00:20:33,405 --> 00:20:36,772
Father, I'll do my best.

268
00:20:39,011 --> 00:20:42,037
Not once, but twice...

269
00:20:43,616 --> 00:20:45,751
So we never got our turn
in the spotlight.

270
00:20:45,751 --> 00:20:48,743
We really have to do
something about that man.

271
00:20:51,557 --> 00:20:53,392
What are you going to do now?

272
00:20:53,392 --> 00:20:54,793
I don't know.

273
00:20:54,793 --> 00:20:57,796
But I'm thinking of staying
here for a while.

274
00:20:57,796 --> 00:21:00,264
Since I have a lot of memories
with my father here, too.

275
00:21:06,472 --> 00:21:07,996
What do you want?!

276
00:21:09,808 --> 00:21:12,845
He'd borrowed money with
this place as collateral?

277
00:21:12,845 --> 00:21:15,848
I have his note right here, too.

278
00:21:15,848 --> 00:21:19,918
It seems he had a lot of expenses
related to expanding the farm.

279
00:21:19,918 --> 00:21:23,222
I told him I didn't need
anything of the sort,

280
00:21:23,222 --> 00:21:26,592
but he insisted on it,
saying it wouldn't feel right otherwise.

281
00:21:26,592 --> 00:21:28,727
That's a damn underhanded thing to do!

282
00:21:28,727 --> 00:21:30,629
How far do you have to take
it before you're satisfied?!

283
00:21:30,629 --> 00:21:33,932
Mr. Murai trusted you to the very end!

284
00:21:33,932 --> 00:21:36,902
And yet, you...You call yourself human?!
You piece of scum!

285
00:21:36,902 --> 00:21:38,233
Stop it!

286
00:21:39,972 --> 00:21:42,634
It doesn't matter now.

287
00:21:44,977 --> 00:21:48,814
Please move out as quickly as you can.

288
00:21:48,814 --> 00:21:51,517
This place is a little more
cleaned up now,

289
00:21:51,517 --> 00:21:54,042
so it should sell for a nice price.

290
00:21:57,089 --> 00:21:58,886
Yuko...

291
00:22:10,469 --> 00:22:12,130
Now, shall we go?

292
00:22:22,114 --> 00:22:25,551
She should've pulled it, after all.

293
00:22:25,551 --> 00:22:29,749
Then Yuko could've stayed
in that house...

294
00:22:34,893 --> 00:22:38,130
It's your fault, you know, Hajime.

295
00:22:38,130 --> 00:22:40,666
There's nothing for you
to worry about.

296
00:22:40,666 --> 00:22:42,657
You'll make friends in no time.

297
00:22:50,943 --> 00:22:52,934
Now, go on in.

298
00:22:56,115 --> 00:23:00,315
That is for you to decide.

299
00:23:13,362 --> 00:23:20,068
Always a dead end

300
00:23:20,068 --> 00:23:26,742
There is no escape

301
00:23:26,742 --> 00:23:34,850
I place my sorrow upon a bird in the sky

302
00:23:34,850 --> 00:23:39,116
And I'll let it fly

303
00:23:43,725 --> 00:23:47,529
This place is ephemeral

304
00:23:47,529 --> 00:23:58,507
An eternity that binds me

305
00:23:58,507 --> 00:24:05,514
Coming or going

306
00:24:05,514 --> 00:24:17,085
All that passes by are dreams

307
00:24:28,336 --> 00:24:30,335
"This is a work of fiction and any
similarities between the names of
characters or organizations in this story
and actual names are entirely coincidental."

308
00:24:31,069 --> 00:24:34,239
There's a memory that
I can't forget.

309
00:24:34,239 --> 00:24:37,409
There's a feeling that
I can't push away.

310
00:24:37,409 --> 00:24:41,847
Tsugumi, I can't tell
you everything yet.

311
00:24:41,847 --> 00:24:43,715
But please understand.

312
00:24:43,715 --> 00:24:47,753
Revenge is wrong.

313
00:24:47,753 --> 00:24:49,688
Hajime...

314
00:24:49,688 --> 00:24:55,490
I don't think getting revenge
is a bad thing.

315
00:24:55,490 --> 00:24:58,493
"Hell Girl
Rain of Remorse"
Next time, "Rain of Remorse".

316
00:24:58,493 --> 00:25:00,993
